inn1.comm: good length, pitches on off, which means the batsman has to play. The ball then slants away. Finds the outside edge and rolls away between second slip and gully
Jarvis now finds the leading edge. Good length, angling, climbs steeply at the batsman. He flicks early and spoons a leading edge to the left of the bowler
much fuller and attacking the stumps, squirts an inside edge to the leg side and gets off the mark does Ahmed
back of a length and running away outside off, Mustafa covers up his off stump and wisely shoulders arms
Mustafa ventures across off stump, picks one off the hips through square leg. Neatly done by the UAE captain

back of a length, angling in towards off, then cunningly straightening away. Ahmed hangs his bat out and is lucky not to nick it. Jarvis already has the crowd buzzing at the HSC. I love this carnival-like atmosphere in Harare
pitched up and angling away outside off, Mustafa drives away from the body and snicks an outside edge past the cordon to third man. The bowler has his hands on his head
Chatara drags his length back and aims for the top of off stump, Ahmed's back-foot punch to cover intervenes
in-between length - neither driveable nor pullable, played up to the covers
Chatara ventures wide of the crease and slants it into the right-hander. He cramps him up for room. Hurriedly jabbed away towards the midwicket region
wide of the crease again, Chatara gets this shortish ball hold its line outside off. Ahmed rides a single down to third man

Is that a statement of intent from the UAE captain? Mustafa comes down, nay runs down the track. Throws Chatara off his length and length. He drags it short and wide outside off. Mustafa reaches out for the ball with his hands and scythes it up and over extra cover. Bam!
full and angling in at off, Ahmed presses forward and defends it down to mid-on
hip-high short ball on the leg stump, Ahmed swats, loses his shape, and only collects fresh air. The ball wanders away behind square off the pad
excellent leave from Mustafa. Good length, starts just outside off and nibbles away late, the left-hander judges it well and lets it go
looks like a slower ball on middle, change-up it is, 107ks, Mustafa waits for the full ball to arrive. Then pats it down
nice and full, angling away outside off, Mustafa shoulders arms again
full on off, tight bowling from Zimbabwe, Mustafa replies with an equally tight front-foot defence to cover
now it's Ahmed's turn to hit over the top. Fullish and outside off, he stays beside the line and pumps it over mid-off inside the circle
chest-high short ball outside off, Ahmed reads the length super quickly. He rocks back and naaaaaails a pull over square leg. Chatara doesn't have enough pace to rush the pull. Positive start for UAE

What a riposte from Chatara. Harare roars in approval. Four, four, and out. Good length, outside off, nibbles away and there's some extra bounce to boot. Ahmed stays beside the line and simply hangs his bat out. Chatara locks his target and finds the outside edge. Taylor moves to his right and snaffles it
full and sprayed into the pads, picked off through midwicket
full and attacking middle, Mustafa plays back and keeps it out
back of a length and slanting away outside off, good extra bounce, no shot again
Jarvis tests Shabbir with a chest-high short ball angling away outside off, he swivels on the back foot, rides the bounce and smartly pulls it in the gap at square leg to fetch three runs
good length and angling away in the channel, Mustafa thought about having a crack at it before swishing his bat away
pitched up and angling away outside off, encourages a drive, scooped off the outside half to cover-point
fuller than a good length and angling away outside off, defensively pushed to mid-on off the front foot
similar length and Jarvis shifts his line wider, the batsman drives away from the body and watches an inside edge streak away square on the leg side
brutal lifter outside off, Ghulam rises with it and flashes it up and over second slip. The ball flies to the third man boundary. Ghulam won't mind the result
Chatara sprays a half-volley on the pads with fine leg up in the circle. That's asking for trouble. Picked off fine of that fielder
follows the half-volley with a sharp bouncer on the leg stump, the batsman ducks under it and evades it
back of a length and slanting away outside off, hint of extra bounce, left alone
back of a length and slanting away outside off, ignored again
short and skidding away outside off, well negotiated by Mustafa. He arches his back, drops his gloves, and lets it go
floats a very full ball down the leg side, beats the batsman's glance, and beats Taylor the keeper to his left. It wasn't far away from the leg stump
full and veering into the pads, flicked in the air but wide of midwicket
full and angling away outside off, tip and run to midwicket. Smart work from UAE
back of a length, jumps off the pitch and cramps the batsman for room, awkwardly fended off
back of a length and angling away outside off, Jarvis finds extra bounce. Mustafa rises with the bat and pats it down calmly
Mustafa dares to foray down the track again. He creates swinging room and launches another one over extra cover. Not middled, just a couple of runs
short and skidding away outside off, Mustafa keeps his eyes locked on the ball before rocking his head out of the way
the short-ball attack continues, angling across off, Mustafa evades it again
good length and largely holds its line on off stump, presses forward and taps it down to mid-off
back of a length and skids on at off stump, Ghulam yanks his bottom hand off the bat and skews it to cover
full and angling across off stump, Ghulam extends his hands and drives it between square cover and mid-off. The ball skips away to the boundary
hip-high short ball on leg stump, swatted away to long leg

back of a length and angling in at off stump, hangs back and defensively drops the ball to short cover. Mustafa eyes up a risky single, Ghulam sends his captain back and rightly so. There wasn't a run
short on off stump, cramps the batsman for room, chopped hastily to short third man
top ball from Jarvis. He continues to challenge both edges, this one whistles past the outside edge. Good length and angling across off, he catches the batsman in the crease, then goes past the bat
much fuller on off stump, presses forward and defends it back down the pitch
full and on the pads, bunted straight to short midwicket
full and shifts his line wider of off, left alone
Jarvis nips another one past the outside edge. Full, draws the batsman forward, he prods at it and is beaten
tight line on off, presses forward and defends to cover
good length on middle from over the wicket, tip and run to short cover. Ghulam and Mustafa keep UAE ticking despite the early wicket
back of a length and running away outside off, ignored in the channel
full and angling across off, no shot again
Muzarabani belts out an lbw appeal, not given because this full ball pitched outside leg. It swings and hits the pad, causing the batsman to fall over
bangs a bouncer on leg, sails over to the keeper, wide called for height
short and outside off, rises on top of the bounce and crisply punches behind point
back of a length on off, forward and blocked solidly to mid-off
short and angling across off, he throws his hands at a pull and flaps it away to third man instead
fuller and slanting away outside off, Ghulam covers his off stump and lets it go
short and outside off, swivels and controls a pull to deep midwicket
slower full ball outside off, run down to third man
full and slanting away in the channel, left alone
full and bang on off - county line and length - forward and played back to the bowler
back of a length on off, hops and fends off to cover
wild full ball, past the marker, off-side wide
back of a length and aiming for the top off, pressed into the covers
on a length and angling across off, he backs away outside leg, creates swinging room and muscles it over the covers
full and swerving down the leg side, tickled to fine leg
shorter and outside off, Ghulam rides the bounce and glides it with the angle to backward point
full and angling across of, Ghulam simply throws his bat at the ball... and only collects fresh air. Static feet, swinging bat
tossed up offbreak, spins away outside off, dabbed with an open face to backward point
much fuller and outside off, squeezed square through the off side for a single
floated up on leg stump, thrusts his bat in front of the pad in defence
straight ball on off stump, gets half-froward and pats it back down the bowler
skids on outside off, stabs the ball away to the off-side sweeper off the back foot
full and sliding into the pads, turned only as far as short midwicket

edged and flies right between the keeper and wide first slip. That was Taylor's catch. He did not even budge. Hamilton dives late to his right but the ball is too wide. Muzarabani sends a back of a length ball that holds its line from round the wicket. The batsman jabs and gets away
short and on the hips, splices a pull to deep midwicket
full and sliding into the pads, tucked around the corner
full on a sixth-stump line outside off, no shot
back of a length and wider outside off, no shot again
back of a length and angling down the leg side for a wide. Fifty stand up between Mustafa and Ghulam
back of a length and targetting the top of off stump, the batsman loosens his grip and defends it back to the bowler
tossed on off, grips, and turns, dead-batted to the off side
flat and skidding into middle and leg, punched solidly to long-on for one
Raza loops it up on off stump, finds grip, and gets it to rip away past the outside edge with extra bounce. A gem of a ball from Raza
shorter and flatter outside off, back-foot force to the covers
nice and full on off stump, ripe for the sweep. Ghulam drops to one knee and pings a slog-sweep against the break over midwicket. Shot!
slower through the air on middle, he plays early and chips it back to the bowler
tossed up and breaks back in to loop off the thigh to the leg side
Cremer roars an appeal for lbw, umpire Raza shakes his head. This was pushed through on middle, spins and bounces to beat the ambitious reverse-sweep and pin the pad. Was it doing too much?
full on middle, kept out
tossed on off, grips, and spins away. This wrong'un is poked to the off side
tossed up higher, spins in to hit the front pad
off-stump yorker, dug out. Cremer begins with a maiden
back of a length and spins away outside off, punched into the covers
full and straight, plays around his front pad and whips the ball to mid-on
skids onto beat the sweep, hit the pad, and sneak away fine on the leg side for a leg bye
straight ball on middle, played back to Raza
full and straight again, quietly worked to the midwicket region
another straight ball, slides in from round the wicket, he plays for turn and is beaten but this seems to be heading past the leg stump
full on off stump, prods forward and nudges it towards the leg side
full on middle stump, backs away to the leg side and smacks it to cover. Ervine - at cover - jumps across to his left and intercepts
good length outside leg, and spinning further away. Extras
full ball, Mustafa reaches at it and defends towards point
good length on middle stump, goes onto the back foot and flicks to square leg
full on off stump, big stride forward and driven to long off. A walking single for these two to collect
full just outside off, Mustafa carefully leans into the defense
full just outside off, gets onto the front foot and defends
tossed up on middle and leg, makes some room to crash this towards the off side, but inside edged onto his pads
full outside off, drags the sweep from outside off. Hit to deep midwicket
good length just outside off, tries to defend, but the ball turns away from him. The ball zips past his bat
full just outside off, driven square to the deep. Shabbir says no to the second run
full on middle, turned off his pads to square leg
full on middle stump, gets onto the front foot and nudges it towards square leg for a quick run
full on middle and leg, driven down the ground to long on. They comfortably walk across
full outside off, and Mustafa goes for the big leg-side heave. Slapped to wide long on this time
good length on middle, and this time it's the one that goes straight through. Tries to adjust after defending down the wrong line, takes the outside edge to point. Zimbabwe won't mind that
full outside off, and swept square! Man in the deep, but falls short of Chatara. Misfield there as the ball spins after bouncing, thereby wrong-footing the fielder. Cremer seems lost for words
full outside off, tries to flick behind leg, but misses
full on leg stump, quick to get down on one knee and sweep, chase for the man at fine leg

breaks the partnership! A reverse sweep one too many.  Pitches full on middle, and hits his front leg as Mustafa misses the shot. Would've gone down to crash into middle. Raza's pumped, and why shouldn't he be? This partnership was cruising along nicely
good length on off stump, defends off the back foot
full on middle stump, big stride forward and blocked
uses his feet! Hits the roof of the grandstand. Tossed up on off and the batsman dances down the wicket, and lifts it over long on
full on off stump, driven down the ground to long on for a single
short outside off, and Shahzad's caught by surprise. Flat-batted down the ground to long off. UAE reach 100
tossed up wide outside off, leans into a drive. Hit to long off
full just outside off, and turning sharply away. Flies past the bat's outside edge and to the keeper
good length on middle stump, and Shahzad tries to defend off the back foot. Hits the shoulder of his bat, and dribbles away to square leg
good length on middle and off, this time he's in position to clip it off his pads to the gap between midwicket and square leg
good length on off and angling across Shabbir. Cut to point
full on off stump, carefully defends off the front foot to see the over off
full on off stump, taps it past the non-striker to mid on
good length on middle stump, defended towards the bowler off the front foot
good length on off stump, gets his front leg across and flicks it to midwicket
good length outside off, but turning away from the left-hander. Shoulders his arms
good length on off, defended off the back foot to Raza
full on middle, drives this towards the on side. Wide enough to beat midwicket, and forces a chase from mid on to cut it off
full on off stump, big stride forward and defend back to the bowler
tossed up on off stump, smothers this with his wrists to work it towards the leg side. Forced to scamper back after looking for the single
flighted on off stump, driven with the drift to wide long off. Gets to the pitch of the ball
full on off stump, and Shahzad tries to work it towards the leg side. Takes a leading edge but well short of the bowler
full on off stump, defended with soft hands back to Cremer
close! Good length on off forces Shahzad to look to defend. He goes onto the back foot but doesn't account for the extra spin. The ball zoots across the bat's face and to the keeper

Raza again! Tries to sweep too fine, and exposed his leg stump. The ball crashes into leg stump as Shabbir misses the sweep completely. It was an enticing full ball that seemed like the perfect length to sweep. But the ball hung in the air just that extra bit, thereby forcing the error from the batsman
good length on leg stump, turned off his pads to short fine leg. Some work for the infielder
full outside off, crunches this drive to short cover, but stopped! Excellent commitment from Mire

one-bounce and into the long-off boundary! Good length on leg stump, but the batsman dances down the wicket to make it a full ball. Once he's there, its all about lifting it over the infield, and Shahzad finds a safe spot over mid off
full on middle stump, driven down the ground to long off
good length on middle, rocks back and punches to midwicket. Stopped by Ervine there
good length on middle stump, turned off his pads to square leg
full on off stump, big stride forward and defended back to Cremer
full on off stump, defended towards the off side. Played towards cover
it's the wrong'un! Zips inwards after pitching outside off. Forces Shaiman to hurry onto the back foot and defended towards point
full on off stump, down on one knee and swept over short fine leg! Over the infielder, and it's a chase. Manages to pull it back
good length on off stump, turned off his pads towards the leg side
full on leg stump, shuffles across to the off side and nudges it to square leg
full on leg stump, driven down the ground to long on for a walking single
full on off stump, defended towards point by Shahzad this time. Opened the bat's face there
full on leg stump, driven off the front foot to mid on
good length on off stump, opens the bat's face and runs it down to third man. Chase for the man inside the circle
full on leg stump, tapped to mid on for a quick run
good length outside off, waits ages for this slower ball and then runs it down to third man. Pokes at it with soft hands
stays low! Full outside off, and Shaiman's defense can't hit the ball. Tries to punch towards the off side but the delivery goes under his bat
full on middle stump, shuffles across to the off side and flicked to deep backward square
good length on off stump, blocked off the back foot towards mid off
huge appeal! Screams his lungs out, but too high I'd reckon. Good length outside off and angling into him. Tries to defend but hits his knee roll. Impact was in front of off though
full just outside off, check drives to mid off
good length on middle stump, punched off the back foot to mid on
good length on middle stump, defended off the back to the bowler
full on off stump, punched back to the bowler
good length outside off, gentle bowling with no spin. Smothered back to the bowler
full on middle stump, punched down the ground to mid on with ease. First single of the over
good length on middle and leg, turned off his pads to the leg side
good length outside off, stands tall and opens his bat's face. Sends this down to third man
back of a length on leg stump, goes down the leg side this time
back of a length outside off, nice bounce off the surface. Shaiman chooses to shoulder his arms as the ball carries through to the keeper. Held on from near chest high
back of a length on off stump, goes onto the back foot and defends with soft hands. Short enough to trouble the batsman
good length outside off, and once again some extra bounce. Tries to turn it towards the leg side but the ball hits his stomach region instead. Ouch
full on leg and going down leg. Taylor and the bowler appeal for lbw but the umpire doesn't think there's been any contact. Defended
short! Pitches outside off, but angling into the batsman. Fended off - with the help of his gloves - from front of his face. Well-directed delivery that would trouble any batsman at any level
good length outside off, pokes at it and taps it towards point
full outside off, but the batsman goes right across that side to sweep it over square leg. Comfortably lifted over the infield
good length just outside off, tries to defend but he's in two minds. Manages to get his bat down, and inside edged onto his pads
whipped! Uses his feet to reach this ball on off stump. Simply smothers this over midwicket, with the use of his wrists, and sends it to the cow-corner boundary
quicker ball, full on off. Carved behind square to backward point
good length on off stump, flicked - but mistimed - towards midwicket
good length outside off, charges down the wicket but checks his shot. Tapped to mid on
good length outside off, pokes at it and sends it fine down to third man
full on middle stump, tapped to midwicket off the front foot
full on off stump, drives early through the line of the ball. Driven to long on
back of a length on middle, tries to hook it square, but misses. Past his glove, and through to the keeper. They appeal for the caught behind, but not given
muscled over Muzarabani! Good length outside off, and smacked over mid on. Shahzad's hit some beautiful shots today
full just outside off, defended off the front foot to the bowler
full outside off, and that's been heaved over cover. Sliced, really, but enough behind it to clear the infield. Won't go to the ropes though
good length on off stump, but Shaiman's quick to spot to length. Swept behind square past short fine leg, and there's a chase for the man there. Can't beat the ball
full just outside off, defended towards the off side
good length on off stump, goes onto the back foot and punches to long on
good length on off stump, carved off the back foot to deep backward point
full on middle, turned towards the leg side
full on off middle stump, makes room to the leg side and lifts this inside-out over cover! Williams isn't happy how that over ended
tossed up on middle and leg, driven to long on for a walking single
full on off stump, turned off his boots to deep backward square. Also the fifty-run partnership
good length outside leg, but turns across the batsman. Extra bounce forces him to misses the defense
good length on off stump, and poked to point. Simply glanced his bat's face open
full on middle stump, takes a few steps down the ground and drives to long on
full on off stump, shuffles across to the off side, and flicks to the leg side
full on off stump, turned towards the leg side with soft hands
back of a length outside off, angling into the batsman and nicely runs it down fine past the keeper's right. A safe shot
lbw appeal! But turned down. Good length outside off and the batsman shoulders his arms. But the ball angles in sharply and hits his front leg. Impact outside off, and too high anyway
good length outside off again, chops it down to third man
short on middle and angling into Shaiman. Going slightly down the leg side, and he pulls this fine! Fine leg's there but he can't stop this from running into the boundary
good length on off stump, punched off the back foot to the bowler
full on off stump, caresses this down the ground to long off
back of a length outside off, cut off the back foot. Hit square but only to point
back of a length outside off, punched off the back foot to long off
good length on middle stump, stays on the back foot, and nudges it to square leg
tossed up on off stump. He's in two minds, but chooses to defend it with the bat's open face
full just outside off, driven down the ground to wide long off. Drinks
back of a length and seams back in from outside off, chops the batsman into half. Beats the inside edge lavishly
Shahzad ventures down the track, Chatara duly pulls his length back and pings the hip
back of a length and outside off, stabbed into the covers
Rameez Shahad brings up an adventurous fifty with an adventurous ramp. Short and outside off, scythed up and over backward point
short on middle, backs away and chops down to short third man
Shahzad rides the bounce of this short ball outside off and directs it to deep third man
back of a length on off, cramps the batsman for room, punched back to Cremer
tossed on middle stump, plays early and skews a leading edge to the left of the diving bowler
flipper on middle, skids in, kept out
tossed outside off, uses his feet and secures a single down to long-of
slower legbreak on off stump, defended off the front foot
Shahzad darts down the track and hacks a short ball from middle to backward square leg off the inside half
Williams doesn't attack the ball at long-on. He hangs back instead of charging in. He winds up conceding a boundary. Sharp short ball, cramps the batsman for room. He splices a pull and gets away
shortish on off stump, chopped away to backward point
short and outside off, opens the face and glides a single down to third man
short on middle, backs away and slashes straight to backward point

The Harare crowd finds its voice again. Rameez Shah backs away a fair way outside leg and aims to go inside-out over mid-off. He can't deal with the extra bounce and ends up splicing it squarer to extra cover. Captain Cremer settles under this skier. Redemption for Chatara after an inconsistent first spell
back of a length and outside off, steered down to third man
full on off, crunched to cover, where the fielder throws himself to his right to stop the ball
floated up on middle, non-turner, brings out the slog-sweep and hits over square leg
fired into leg stump, does not connect with the flick and wears it on the front pad
ventures down the track, manufactures a low full-toss, and creams it in the gap between wide long-off and deep cover. Excellent timing
shimmies out and drives a full ball down to long-off

Such swift work from Taylor behind the stumps. He rides the bounce and breaks the bails off. Cremer looped up a googly outside off, drew the batsman forward, and had him overbalanced, but Usman dragged his back leg in time to save himself
back of a length on middle, punched off the back foot to mid-on
off-stump yorker, dug out
floated up on off, not much turn, smothered off the front foot
pushed through on middle, tapped to the off side off the front foot
shorter offbreak, punched to short cover, where Cremer puts in a tumbling stop
Raza drops it short and outside off, spins away, the batsman can't control a cut. He top-edges between backward point and short third man
pushed through on off, eases forward and drives a single down to long-off
floated up on leg stump, presses forward and smothers it

Holes out to deep midwicket. Look at the jubilant crowd. Carnival-like atmosphere at the HSC, I repeat. This wasn't a great ball, though. Half-tracker on middle stump, instead of swatting it into the stands Usman pulls straight down the throat of Ervine at deep midwicket
good length on leg stump, flicked to the leg side
good length on leg stump again, tapped to square leg this time
full on leg stump, clipped off his pads to deep midwicket
full on middle stump, driven down the ground to long off
full outside leg, flicked off his pads to square leg
full on off stump, muscled towards long on for a walking single

pulled but taken in the deep! Short on middle, but entices the batsman to pull. Hit well off the back foot, but doesn't have the distance. Would've dropped short of Muzarabani, but he commits to the catch, and dives foward to complete it
sliding into leg stump from round the wicket, blocked to midwicket
slow turn for Raza, dabbed with the break to square leg
flat and short on middle, whipped away behind square leg
flighted on middle, stays leg-side of this full ball and drives down to long-off
full and outside off, rolls out his wrists, and sweeps to deep square leg
steps down the track and drives a full ball down to long-on
short and on leg stump, hangs back and punches down to long-on
straight ball on middle, blocked to the leg side
short and holds its line outside off, chopped to deep third man
slower bouncer outside off, Ahmed swings early and only collects fresh air
back of a length at off stump, jabbed down to long-on for a single
full on middle, tip and run to midwicket
floated full and outside off, right in the slot for the drive. Ahmed makes swinging room and crunnnnnches between short cover and mid-off
back of a length on off, chopped to third man
short of a length and angling in at off stump, defended to cover
back of a length and bounces at off, turns the batsman inside out, prodded to the off side
sharp short ball outside off, beats Raza's weak hook

Raza jumps onto Muzarabani. I love this crowd at the HSC. They go berserk again. Another UAE batsman has been bounced out. This was short and outside off, he fetches it from there and miscues a pull to Mire at deep square leg
back of a length on off, defended
short and outside off, the batsman has a big swish at it... and misses. More activity among the groundstaff. This does not look good at the HSC
Mufti rides the bounce of this short ball outside off and steers down to third man
dug in short and outside off, more effort in this lifter, he arches his back and ramps it over the vacant cordon to the third man fence
back of a length on middle, Naveed clears his front leg and tonks it over the bowler's head. Dismissive. Back-to-back fours for Naveed
It's raining boundaries in Harare. Afghanistan and Ireland will be rooting for Naveed and UAE. He hangs back and pulls this chest-high short ball to the square leg boundary
slower ball on off, tipped to cover-point for one
wide of the crease, Jarvis gets this full ball to hold its line outside off and skip past the outside edge as the batsman drives and does not make contact

Muzarabani nearly bounces out Naveed. Raza misjudges this skier and drops it. Banged in short and outside off, Naveed backs away and swings it hiiiiiiigh into the gloomy skies. The ball drops down and Raza drops it. He does not even get his hands to it. The ball bursts through, hits his shoulder, and spills down
shortish, outside off, chopped away to backward point
dragged short and outside off, Naveed winds up and utterly batters it over deep square leg for a mighty six. Muscled into the stands
full and outside off, pushed into the covers
short at the hips, whipped through square leg for a single

inn2.comm: wide of the crease, back of a length and straightens outside off, gets on top of the bounce and solidly punches past backward point. Over to the passionate Harare crowd. Whoa! Look at them
much fuller and outside off, presses forward and bunts it into the covers for one
shorter and angling into the body of Hamilton, he sits back and fends the ball away
very full and swings in to off stump, Hamilton deploys a good stride and blocks it back to the right of Naveed
full outswinger, pitches on a fourth-stump line and nibbles away at nearly 140ks, Hamilton judges it well and lets it go
short and aimed at the chest, Hamilton fends it to the leg side
back of a length and wide outside off, Mire goes chasing after it with static feet and watches the ball move past the outside edge
and again. Back of a length on a sixth-stump line, swings with no feet, and misses

back of a length, much closer to off, Mire gets beside the line and punches crisply through the gap at the covers. The fielder chases hard and slides the ball in even as he tumbles beyond the boundary
good length and nibbles away outside off, watchfully left alone
back of a length and swinging into the pads, Hamilton plays all around it and takes it on the the front pad as the ball wanders away to square leg
back of a length on off, punched down to mid-off

Naveed beats Mire for pace and rushes a hook. The resultant top edge is well held by square leg. 137ks short ball, fizzes through outside off, Mire has to fetch it from outside off and is late onto his shot. Gone. What an early lift for UAE
back of a length and outside off, run away behind point
back of a length and outside off, Moor busily punches the ball to the right of deep third man
on a length and outside off, deftly dabbed to the left of third man now
lovely delivery from Naveed. Good length, angling into Hamilton, the batsman plays for the angle but the ball zips away late and moves past the outside edge
wide of the crease, tactful use of the crease, full and angling in on off, Hamilton presses forward and taps it to cover-point
fuller and outside off, punched through the line to mid-off
gentle outswinger, left alone outside off
short, wide, slashed away but Moor can't get it past backward point
back of a length and outside off, Moor extends his hands and engages in a back-foot force through cover-point
good length on a fifth-stump line, left alone in the channel
full outswinger, left alone outside off again
back of a length and angling in, dabbed to backward point
chest-high short ball on off stump, Naveed is troubling the batsmen with pace and bounce. Hamilton aims a pull, instead he splices the ball in the air to the right of mid-on
Naveed hits a hard length and as a result hits the bat hard. Defended behind square on the off side
shorter and outside off, Hamilton gets on top of the bounce and powerfully flat-bats it away past mid-off. The outfield isn't really quick but it isn't really slow either after the rain
overpitched and outside off, Hamilton presses forward and drives the ball straight to cover

Naveed hits 140ks and floors Hamilton's off stump. In-between length from Naveed again - neither driveable nor pullable - it keeps low to boot. Starts outside off and cuts back in to shoot through the defences of the opener. Zimbabwe lose their openers and the asking rate has nudged past 6
on a length and outside off, tapped to cover off the front foot
back of a length and outside off, punched to deep third man's right
full and angling in at off, blocked to the leg side
very full on off stump, pushed down to mid-on
good length and outside off, no shot
full and wide outside off, skewed off the inside half to mid-on
good length and angling in on middle, played to mid-on
short, wide, gets on top and cuts to third man's right
Taylor shuffles across and works a length ball to midwicket
very full and sliding in, inside-edged onto the thigh. Replays suggest no nick. Height could have been an issue there
short and wide, under-edges a cut behind to the keeper
full and angling in, deflected to square leg and gets off the mark after eight balls
back of a length and outside off, punches wide of mid-off
full on off, shuffles across and clips to short midwicket
short, wide, slashed to third man's right
full offcutter slanting down leg, wide
good length and outside off, left alone
full and zipping through the channel, Taylor protects his off stump and lets it go
back of a length and outside off, Taylor flat-bats it straight to mid-off
starts off with a top inswinging yorker, Moor squeezes an inside edge onto the boot. Taylor pulls him through for a hasty single
good length on off stump, blocked back to the bowler
tucked off the pads to deep square leg for one
brutal lifter aimed at the armpit, Moor takes his eyes off it, looks away, and cops a blow on the shoulder
back of a length and attached with width outside off, smeared to backward point
bouncer down leg, wide called
back of a length and outside off, Moor gets on top of the bounce and cuts the ball away to the left of backward point and right of deep third man
full and drifts in on off, no turn, presses forward and blocks it back to the bowler
arm ball, arrows in on middle, Taylor covers up in defence
nurdled off the pads to the right of short midwicket for a risky single
slider on middle, full, forward defence
slower on off stump, forward and driven down to long-off
Taylor goes low, drags a sweep from outside off to short fine leg where there is a fumble
back of a length and width outside off, Taylor unleashes a fierce cut to the left of backward point and right of deep third man. Thwack
full and swerves back in, Taylor drives outside the line and inside-edges it onto the pad
pitched up and outside off, rocks forward and drills a drive to cover
back of a length and angling in, Taylor gets inside the line and neatly tucks the ball through square leg
back of a length on off, played back down the pitch
cuts back in sharply, another inside edge onto the back pad
full on off stump, collapses his back leg and drives inside out, along the ground, to wide long-off
back of a length and outside off, forced to the right of long-off
slower through the air, drifting in at off, turning away, Taylor slices his loft. Falls to the right of sweeper cover. The ball plugs in the deep

Ahmed Raza bursts through the defences of Taylor. The defeated batsman sumps to his knees. What a crucial blow. This was the quick fizzer, sliding in with the arm, Taylor plays for turn and watches the ball break through his defences. UAE are charged up. The Harare crowd has been hushed into silence
fired on off stump, kept out
fuller and outside off, forward and pushed into the covers
really full on off stump, dug out
Mustafa goes up for an lbw appeal. He believes he has his man. This was tossed up and breaks back in, no inside edge, and he his hit on the pad just outside the line of off
very full and outside off, Williams squeezes a drive to sweeper cover
worked with the spin to short fine leg
overpitched on off, belted straight to short cover
slower and dips at off stump, forward and smothered
slides on outside off, Williams plays for turn and is beaten on the outside edge
shorter and outside off, punched off the back foot to mid-off
pushed through outside off, patted to cover off the front foot
whipped with the spin to wide long-on
reverse-swept from the stumps wide of slip
back of a length and slides in, nearly chops it back onto the stumps
on a length and outside off, presses forward and lets the ball slide off the face to backward point
Williams ventures a reverse-sweep and gets it past slip again
pushed through on off, eased down to long-off
low full-toss on middle, clipped away to midwicket
back of a length and speared on off stump, punched back to the bowler
length ball on off, non-turner, defended back to him
skids on just a shade outside off, prodded back to Raza
drifts in on middle, defended gingerly to the leg side
full on middle, pushed down to long-off
whipped from outside off to deep midwicket off the front foot
speared in on middle, clipped off the back foot to midwicket
arm ball, hits the pad, but this is heading down the leg side
too full for the reverse-sweep, but is pinned on the pad, hit outside the line of off
zips through outside off, the extra bounce beats the cut. Anxious shots from Zimbabwe's batsmen
tossed on middle, shimmies out and drives it back to the bowler
on a length and outside off, driven off the front foot to the right of long-off
shortish and outside off, slashed away behind point, the crowd buzzing again
back of a length on off stump, punched down the ground. That's drinks
full just outside off, driven away from him to deep extra cover
full, but wide outside off. Tapped off the front foot to the vacant area near cover
full on off stump, prods forward and defends towards the off side
tossed up on leg stump, pushed past the non-striker to long on. They want the second, but not this time
reverse swept, but not hit well. Full on off stump, and slapped to short third man. They scamper across
another reverse sweep, this time it goes to point. Full on middle, and swept straight to the infielder
floated up on middle, driven back to the bowler
short on a fourth-stump line, shifts back and punches to extra cover
off-stump yorker, dug out to point
full on middle, Williams brings out his favourite reverse sweep and sends it fine of backward point. Rolled out his wrists and guided it away
on a length and outside off, eases forward and secures a single down to long-off
flat dart on middle, chipped back to the bowler
paddled from middle and leg to short fine's left
poked to backward point off an outside edge
slid through outside off, back-foot punch down to long-off
tossed outside off, eases forward and drives to mid-off
shorter and skids on outside off, chopped away behind point. They apply pressure on the fielder. He fumbles and allows an easy double in the end
tapped down to long-on for a jogged single
full and sliding away outside off with the angle, Williams has a skittish poke and watches the ball beat the outside edge
short, wide, Williams throws his bat at the ball and still can't connect
back of a length and outside off, laced to sweeper cover
very full on off, Moor hangs back, opens the face and guides the ball through the covers
full one, dipping at leg stump, worked away behind square
back of a length and on the hips, glanced to fine leg
back of a length and just a shade outside off, stabbed back to the bowler
tossed up higher outside off, tapped to cover
back of a length and slides on off, punched up to cover again
skids into leg stump, forced down to long-on
floated up outside off, spins in, blocked back to the bowler
non-turner outside off, full, Williams brings out a reverse-sweep. Nearly picks it off the keeper's gloves and sends it away fine. Deftly done
short on middle, blocked to cover
back of a length and outside off, hit to third man
good length, starts outside off, and skids back in, turns him inside out and hit him high on the pad
full and outside off, helped off the face to backward point
short on middle stump, worked away behind square on the leg side
short and outside off, flat-batted down to mid-off
back of a length and spins back in, forced to short midwicket
pushed to short midwicket's right with the spin
clipped off the pads to deep midwicket
on a length and spins away outside off, Moor sizes it up and creams it away between sweeper cover and wide long-off. What a way to bring up a fifty stand
pushed through on middle, stroked to the right of the bowler
chipped away to deep square leg. 100 up for the hosts
shortish on the hips, swatted away to deep square leg. Shahzad attacks the ball and keeps them to one
short and outside off, rides the bounce and steers to deep third man
full and nibbling in on middle, slower ball, defended back

short and wide outside off, Williams jumps off the ground and ramps it all the way over deep third man. HSC raises itself to a massive roar. Taylor is up on is feet. Ladies and gents, that's the first six of the chase. Asking rate under 8
full and skidding into the pads, picked off to deep square leg. A misfields allows an easy two
slower cutter outside off, jabbed into the covers
really full on off, whipped away to wide long-on. Moor wants two, his partner sends him back
really full on middle, Williams sweeps from the stumps. He rolls out his wrists and guides it through backward square leg. Precise placement and timing to boot
fuller on off, pushed back to the bowler
near yorker on off, jammed out to long-on
speared on off, hit down to long-on
middle-stump yorker, dug out
back of a length on off stump, angling in and cramping the batsman for room. Punched off the back foot
good length outside off, but jagging in. Tapped to cover with soft hands and Moor scampers across to the other side
good length on off, and angling across the left-hander, carved off the back foot to deep backward point. Couple more
full and wide outside off, crunched off the front foot to deep extra cover. Great sound off the bat, but straight to the man in the deep

full on leg stump, tries to whip this fine down the leg side but can't connect. The keeper's dive to his left stops the ball from going past him. Wide not signalled, and that's an excellent decision! Came off the boot
full outside off, and angling into the right-hander. Cut off the back foot, but no direction behind that shot. Straight to point
goes short on middle stump! Forces Williams to drop his knees and get under the line of the ball
slower ball, full outside off. Caressed to deep extra cover for a run. And that's Williams' fifty
good length outside off, and that's punched well! Beats cover to go to the man in the deep, but Moor manages to take the second

Moor falls! And that's a soft dismissal at cover. Overpitched on off stump, and he tries to bunt it over the infield. Manages to take the bat's toe end, and sits up as an easy catch for the fielder. Silence once again at the HSC
starts off with the short ball, but he oversteps! Goes over Raza's shoulder, but earns a free run for his team
full and wide, overpitched outside off. Tapped with the square bat to point. Tough to put that length away
back of a length, and wide outside off. Drags his pull - along the ground - to deep midwicket
play and miss. Full outside off, and tails inwards oh-so-slightly. Tries to drive past cover, but plays down the wrong line. The ball goes between bat and pad
good length on off, and jags sharply inwards. Chopped on to the leg side behind the batsman
good length outside off, tries to pull, but mistimes this shot! Trickles away to midwicket. An excellent start to Naveed's over
full on off stump, driven down the ground, as they take off for the single. Long off intercepts
full and slow outside off, and Williams crunches this past cover! Caresses this through the line of the ball, and goes swiftly into the extra-cover boundary.
full outside off, and driven square once again. Hit too square on this occasion. Man in the deep
full outside off, with the bowler rolling his fingers over this delivery. Smothered to deep extra cover
full just outside off, tapped past the non-striker to long on. They push for two, and complete it easily
back of a length outside off, but it's the change up. Williams is through his pull too early as the ball zips under his arm and through to the keeper

slower ball, full on off stump again. Driven to mid off, but they take the quick single. Hit wicket from the infielder though! Time for the third umpire. Williams didn't drag his bat in - but instead popped it in - and that was the question that the third umpire had to answer. Replays suggest he's safe

good length outside off, and cut off the back foot. Going for the four near the point-boundary, but the ball slows down near the soggy outfield. Misfield in the deep, too, but Zimbabwe stick to only a double
good length on off stump, angling into Raza and punched to mid on
short outside off, and Raza rides the bounce to cut this over point. Hit in front of square, forcing the outfielder to intercept to his right
full on leg stump, and that's been muscled to the leg side. An on-drive that beats midwicket's left. Racing away to the cow corner boundary!
back of a length outside off, rocks back and mistimes his pull to long on. Only a single this time
slower ball, full on off. Tapped past the non-striker to mid on. They take a quick single

back of a length outside off, enough width to slash at it, and it's been top edged to third man. The fielder in the deep slides across the ground and stops the ball. Rocket throw at the keeper's end ensures the batsmen can't take the extra run
slower ball, on a good length. Pitches outside off, and worked to mid on for a jogging single
slower ball, full outside off. Tapped to cover for a quick run. Smart bowling
slower ball, full on off stump. Raza wanted to slog this towards the leg side, but checks his shot. Whips this check-drive to long on
good length outside off, and that's been pulled to deep midwicket. The outfield slows the shot down once again
good length on middle stump, tries to paddle this towards square leg, but doesn't connect. Hits his gut, and trickles away to the off side
full on middle and leg, but whipped off his pads! There's the boundary they needed, and Raza's used his wrists to flick this over midwicket. The fielder in the deep can't do anything
short and wide outside off, flat-batted past the bowler's left to long off
full on leg stump, driven along the carpet to long on. They walk across for the single
overpitched full outside off. Quick delivery this time that's almost a yorker. Squeezed away to the off side
five free runs! Saw Raza shuffling in his crease and Mustafa bowls full and wide outside leg stump. Raza doesn't do anything, but the keeper can't hold on to it either. How important is that
full outside off, crunches this drive to deep extra cover. Williams is struggling while running. Cramps, perhaps?
full just outside off, caressed to deep extra cover once again
overpitched outside off, driven to cover. Man there
full on middle stump, driven to wide long on for two with Williams hobbling back in time. Twelve off that over
starts off with the slower ball. It's full on off, and angling into Raza. Whipped to deep midwicket
back of a length outside off, slower ball again. Williams drags his pull to deep midwicket. Raza wants the second, but Williams can't come back. Fifty partnership in just 36 balls.
gold dust! Sticks with the slower ball, but changes the length. Short outside off and Raza misses the leg-side drag
short outside off once again, connects with his drag towards the leg side on this occasion. Flat-batted to deep midwicket
full on off stump, tapped past the non-striker's left to long on
overpitched just outside off, charges down the wicket and taps it to deep extra cover. Only a single
it's on the roof! And the Harare crowd comes alive. Full on off stump, and he simply gets his front foot out of the way before slogging through the ball's line. Over long on!
overpitched on leg stump. Almost a yorker this time. Tapped to long on, but Williams is running hard! Makes the second run just in time before the bowler can take his bails off
straight to deep backward square! Full toss on off, and Raza swivels to pull square. Hit well, but no elevation behind that shot. Straight down the fielder's throat. Another twist?
full just outside off, drives but comes off the bat's toe end. Down to long on
full outside off, crunches this drive away from his body. But stopped at cover
full on middle stump, reverse swept to point but the throw's at the wrong end! Directs his throw at the keeper's end, but Ervine's the fitter man. The fielder should've gone to the non-striker's end

slower ball full on off stump, tapped to wide long off but it's all happening now! Sean Williams turned for the second, but collided with the bowler - who was trying to get to the stumps - manages to get back to the crease though. Safe in the end
full and wide outside off again. Forced to reach at it, and sent to long off. Williams has a word with the bowler at the non-striker's end
full on middle and angling down leg, flicked to square leg. They want the second, but that would've been suicidal
full on middle stump, driven to mid on
good length on off stump, turned off his pads to deep midwicket. Enough time to motor back for the second
good length on off and the ball jags into the left-hander. Tries to punch off the back foot but inside-edged onto his pads. The ball's somewhere, and they scamper across for the run
crashed past the umpire! Tossed up on off, and he smacks this through the ball's line. Full follow through of the bat, and flies into the straight boundary
low full toss just outside leg, bunted to long on. Also the team 200
low full toss on middle, and that's been reverse swept to point
low full toss on leg stump, backs away and smacks this down the ground again. Almost takes the non-striker with him. Straight to long on this time
and the crowd's come alive once again! Full on middle and leg, and Williams sweeps this over short fine leg! No one in the deep and the spectators are dancing

one-handed stunner! Williams falls for 80. Good length on middle, and he tried to paddle this over short fine leg again. Off the bat's top half, and Amir runs backwards and sticks his right hand out. Sticks in his palm!
good length on middle stump, caressed to deep extra cover off the front foot
full on off stump, defended with soft hands. Played back to the bowler
good length on off stump, tucked off his pads to deep midwicket. Just a single
crashes into middle stump! Back of a length on off, and Cremer's pull takes the bottom edge of the bat. Straight into the stumps and the Zimbabwe captain has to go
good length on off stump, tails slightly inwards. Tries to defend towards the leg side, but inside edged onto his pads. Appeal for lbw turned down but they scamper across for the run
full on off stump, turned off his boots to deep midwicket. He'll keep strike
back of a length outside off, mistimes his back-foot punch towards point. Only a single, and gets Jarvis back on strike
almost a yorker, and that's been bunted back to the bowler. Full and straight on off stump. Can't do much with that
full outside off, and mistimes his drive to point. Gives Ervine the strike once again
short outside off, but Ervine can't connect! Slower ball that loops over the batsman's attempted pull. This'll hurt Zimbabwe
low full toss outside leg stump, clipped off his pads to deep midwicket
full outside off and driven to long off. Just a single, with Mustafa fielding in the deep. Zimbabwe need 15 off the final over
full on off and that's been muscled towards the on side. Dribbles down to wide long on
low full toss outside leg, clipped to deep midwicket. Zimbabwe need 12 off four
through to the third-man boundary! It ain't over just yet. Naveed delivers a ful toss on off stump, and Ervine's big heave takes the outside edge. Zimbabwe will take that
low ful toss on middle stump, smacked to cover for a single but all they can do is take a single
full outside off, and slapped down the ground to long off

full toss outside off, sliced over point and they only take a couple. UAE win! Zimbabwe lose by three runs, but they're not out yet. If tomorrow's game is tied, then they'd go through. But it doesn't look good for Zimbabwe right now: they're on the brink of elimination
